Blocks.childText: 314 FAITH OF OUR FATHERS. 2. Our Fathers, chained in prisons dark, Were still in heart and conscience free: How sweet would be their children's fate, If they, like them, could die for thee ! Faith of our Fathers ! Holy Faith ! We will be true to thee till death. 3. Faith of our Fathers ! Mary's prayers Shall win our country back to thee; And through the truth that comes from God England shall then indeed be free. Faith of our Fathers! Holy Faith ! We will be true to thee till death. 4. Faith of our Fathers ! we will love Both friend and foe in all our strife : And preach thee too, as love knows how By kindly words and virtuous life : Faith of our Fathers ! Holy Faith ! We will be true to thee till death.
